Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{3%cloves}(minced). Cut @tomato{1}(cut into 1/4-inch-thick wedges). Peel and thinly slice half the @onion{1}(sliced); finely dice remaining onion. Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}(diced into 1/4-inch pieces).

== Jasmine Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add 1 tsp garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Tomato Salad ==

While rice cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, sliced onion, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

== Black Beans ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a second small #pot over medium-high heat. Add green pepper, diced onion, @Loisa Sazón Organic Seasoning{1%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and slightly tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @black beans{1%unit} and their liquid and @sugar{1/4%tsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until warmed through and slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chicken Cutlets ==

While beans cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Season all over with remaining @Loisa Sazón Organic Seasoning{1}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If the chicken begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} and let rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

== Garlic Oil ==

Meanwhile, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine remaining garlic, @cooking oil{2%tbsp}, and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{60%seconds}. Carefully uncover and stir.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide rice, beans, and tomato salad (draining first) between plates in separate sections. Top rice with chicken and drizzle with garlic oil. Serve.

> Slice chicken crosswise before serving.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.